-- LivePerson Rises to Highest Since Listing on U.S. Share Gain
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-02-15T13:47:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/liveperson-rises-to-highest-since-listing-on-u-s-share-gain.html
LivePerson Inc. (LPSN) , an Israeli provider
of real-time chats and voice customer-service software, surged
to the highest since the shares were listed in March, closing
the gap with the U.S.-traded shares.  The stock  gained 14 percent to 55.95 shekels, or the
equivalent of $14.96, at 3:36 p.m. in  Tel Aviv . The New York-
traded shares advanced 19 percent to $14.96 yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
